{
  "stem": "19969.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in, in December of-- just the day before Christmas in 1944, my battalion pushed into Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I wasn't the first.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were other American units that had already crossed the day before.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in my attack zone, I crossed the day before Christmas.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went-- got into Germany then, and the next few days several miles.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we thought we were-- finally cracked the worst of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then came the Battle of the Bulge.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Germans made a desperate attempt to break through the troops on them, which were way over to our left attacking into-- through Belgium.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that stalled everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then we had to pull some troops out of our army to send over to help the troops that were being attacked on our left.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were stripped of troops, and-- to try to reinforce the Bulge.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that, that Bulge was finally stopped by, by Christmas, actually.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It would-- or right after Christmas, it was pretty well stopped.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then the Germans made a second attack in our sector, which they called Operation North Wind.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had a new division that had just come over from the States up in the Vosges Mountains.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Germans attacked that division and pushed it back some 5 or 10 miles.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So suddenly, I got an order-- I'm up in Germany now, and-- that I had to pull back because we were fairly exposed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our division was up there by itself in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, well, the whole division was ordered back and immediately ordered to counter-attack the German penetration.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I got back one afternoon from Germany by trucks and hit the German penetration the next morning.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was in January of '45.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
